              "relation": "NE",
              "compareValue": "*NONE"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "CNNTYPE",
      "description": "Connection type",
      "help": "Connection type (CNNTYPE)\n\nSpecifies the type of connection with the remote system.\n\nNote: The operating system no longer supports IPX, this value will be ignored.\n\n指定できる特殊値: *SAME, *SNA, *IP, *IPX, *USRDFN",
      "inputType": "text",
      "required": false,
      "defaultValue": "*SAME",
      "attributes": {
        "characterSet": "upper",
        "maxLength": 8
      },
      "promptControl": [
        {
          "controlParameter": "RMTSYS",
          "countRelation": "EQ",
          "count": 1,
          "conditions": [
            {
              "relation": "NE",
              "compareValue": "*NONE"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "DESTTYPE",
      "description": "Destination type",
      "help": "Destination type (DESTTYPE)\n\nSpecifies the type of the remote system (RMTSYS parameter). This parameter, along with the type of data contained in the spooled file (DEVTYPE parameter on the CRTPRTF command), is used by a remote writer to determine the format used to send the spooled file. The spooled file will be held by the remote writer if the type of data in the spooled file is not supported by the system.\n\nNote: This value should be specified when possible, to allow the greatest flexibility when selecting values for other parameters.\n\nNote: This value is valid only when the CNNTYPE is *IP or *USRDFN.\n\nNote: This value is not valid when CNNTYPE(*IPX) is specified.\n\n指定できる特殊値: *SAME, *OS400, *OS400V2, *PSF2, *S390, *NETWARE3, *NDS, *OTHER",
      "inputType": "text",
      "required": false,
      "defaultValue": "*SAME",
      "attributes": {
        "characterSet": "upper",
        "maxLength": 10
      },
      "promptControl": [
        {
          "controlParameter": "RMTSYS",
          "countRelation": "EQ",
          "count": 1,
          "conditions": [
            {
              "relation": "NE",
              "compareValue": "*NONE"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "TRANSFORM",
      "description": "Host print transform",
      "help": "Transform SCS to ASCII (TRANSFORM)\n\nSpecifies whether to make use of the host print transform function to transform a spooled file of device type *SCS into ASCII data when the file is sent to a remote printer queue.\n\nNote: This parameter is not valid when the CNNTYPE is specified as *SNA or *NONE.",
